    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Commonly defined as large frame saws whose saw web is set in the middle of a wood frame; used for cutting veneer from wood. The term also refers to a kind of backsaw with a slightly curved blade and a heavy wood back that serves as a handle. It is also a particular kind of circular saw.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000036401/Salaman, Dictionary of Tools Used in Woodworking (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zagen met enigszins gebogen blad en een zware houten rug die als handvat fungeert om fineerbladen te zagen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
